    "For a black hole mass of 1.2 × 10 9 M, this is consistent with the inner edge of the disc or smaller.",
    "As Chandra has observed and followed-up on more lensed quasars and the light curve method has been applied to many of them, it is clear that a compact size for the X-ray emitting region is common for all systems observed to date, typically within 10 r g or less.",
    "A summary of the results so far is given in Table 2.",
    "The Fe Kα reflection feature is one of the best probes we have of the inner edge of the accretion disc.",
    "Detection and possible microlensing of this emission feature has been reported for H1413+117 (Oshima et al. 2001; Chartas et al. 2004 Chartas et al., 2007)), MG J0414+0534 (Chartas et al. 2002), QSO 2237+0305 (Dai et al. 2003; Chen et al. 2012), SDSS J1004+4112 (Ota et al. 2006; Chen et al. 2012), RXJ 1131-1231 (Chartas et al. 2012), QJ 0158-4325, HE 0435-1223, SDSS J0924+0219, and HE 1104 -1805 (Chen et al. 2012)."
